b'2014/2015\n\nLewandowski\xe2\x80\x99s first season at Bayern was far from his most productive season, but 38 G+A is far from poor. https://t.co/jC8KmRHb0A'

b'2011/2012\n\nPrior to this season, nobody really knew about Lewandowski or his potential, but by the end of a season in which he scored 30 goals and got 12 assists, helping Dortmund win the Bundesliga and the DFB Pokal (where he scored a hattrick against Bayern), that all changed. https://t.co/U54QudDJHj'

b'2018/2019\n\nWhile his 18/19 season wasn\xe2\x80\x99t as prolific in terms of goals (40), he registered an impressive 13 assists across the season. Despite a turbulent season for the club, Lewandowski\xe2\x80\x99s crucial goals helped Bayern achieve a domestic double. https://t.co/yGN87WcpfY'

b'2017/2018\n\nDespite a switch of managers, Lewandowski remained as reliable as ever in front of goal as he found the back of the net 41 times over the course of the season for Bayern Munich. Unfortunately, he and his teammates faltered horribly against Real Madrid in the UCL. https://t.co/jxImaDRde8'

b'2012/2013\n\nLewandowski\xe2\x80\x99s penultimate season with Dortmund was what really put him on the map. Although his 36 goals and 13 assists were unable to secure silverware for BVB, he brought them within touching distance of it with some iconic performances (4 goals vs. Real Madrid \xf0\x9f\x91\x80). https://t.co/rjAbImWtKH'

b'2015/2016\n\nThis was Lewandowski\xe2\x80\x99s true arrival at Bayern Munich. In his second season at the club, he played a huge role in Bayern\xe2\x80\x99s Bundesliga and DFB Pokal triumphs, plundering 42 goals in all competitions for Bayern. https://t.co/jrcNI1TcGn'

b'2019/2020\n\nAlthough his 2020/21 Bundesliga campaign was far better than his 19/20 one, it\xe2\x80\x99s Lewandowski\xe2\x80\x99s performances in the UCL (10 games, 15 goals, 6 assists) which make this his greatest season ever. Add that to the fact he won every trophy available. https://t.co/2MS8QsdmWY'
